```php
class SerializedORM
{
    private $data = [];

    public function __call($method, $args)
    {
        if (preg_match('/^(get|set)(\w+)$/', $method, $matches)) {
            $property = strtolower($matches[2]);
            switch ($matches[1]) {
                case 'get':
                    return isset($this->data[$property]) ? unserialize($this->data[$property]) : null;
                case 'set':
                    $this->data[$property] = serialize($args[0]);
                    break;
            }
        }
    }

    public function save($file, $chunkSize = 1000)
    {
        $handle = fopen($file, 'wb');
        if ($handle === false) {
            throw new Exception("Unable to open file for writing: {$file}");
        }
        $count = 0;
        foreach ($this->data as $key => $value) {
            fwrite($handle, serialize([$key, $value]));
            if (++$count % $chunkSize == 0) {
                fflush($handle);
            }
        }
        fflush($handle);
        fclose($handle);
    }

    public function load($file, $chunkSize = 1000)
    {
        $handle = fopen($file, 'rb');
        if ($handle === false) {
            throw new Exception("Unable to open file for reading: {$file}");
        }
        while (!feof($handle)) {
            $chunk = fread($handle, $chunkSize);
            $data = [];
            foreach (unserialize($chunk) as $row) {
                $data[$row[0]] = $row[1];
            }
            $this->data = array_merge($this->data, $data);
        }
        fclose($handle);
    }

    public function delete($key)
    {
        unset($this->data[$key]);
    }

    public function clear()
    {
        $this->data = [];
    }
}
```
In this version, the `save()` method opens the file in binary mode for writing and writes the data in chunks of `$chunkSize` records. After writing each chunk, it calls the `fflush()` function to ensure that the data is written to disk. The `load()` method reads the file in chunks of `$chunkSize` bytes and unserializes the data into an array, which is merged with the existing data array.

Here's an example of how to use the updated class:
